      {
        "id": 3142259,
        "name": "Peter Chiu",
        "username": "Peter_Chiu",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/8dc957/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-04-11T14:40:10.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Nice TNs\u2026I never had tried his white and red.</p>\n<p>My prefer Rully is  from Jaeger-Defaix; but sadly\u2026they do not come every year. The red used to be around $ 38 in 2014.  His white were at around $ 42 to $44 for vintage 2014 and 2016.</p>\n<p>Since you own multiple bottles of the white\u2026how about matching it with a white Ladoix by Chevalier 2017 at $ 49.75? The Ladoix white does not come here too often and it is from 2017. Jasper Morris ( page 289 Inside Burgundy) calls the whites are the strength of the Domaine  ( based in Ladoix) and that they are bright, stylish wines with good concentration.</p>\n<p>But personally I much prefer all his reds. They are <em>value</em> wines - when compare the same wines with other producers. The Domaine has only one red G-cru - Corton Le Rognet 2015 (Mgm) was at $264 when other red Cortons ( for sinple bottle of 750 ml) from vintage  2016-2017 at between $160 to $ 180. The last time the simple bottle  (of his G-cru)  came was for vintage 2013 at $ 138.  I still have one bottle of his 2005 ( a $98 ) left.</p>",
